RACE.FOOTNOTES: KEEP YOUR COIL took control quickly from inside, led two wide into the lane, remained clear into the final furlong under left handed urging and was never challenged. HENNYS CRAZY TRAIN stalked the pacesetter outside a pair of rivals, took aim three wide into the lane but could not threaten the winner in the final furlong while clearly second best. ANNIE'S SONG (IRE) stalked between rivals into and around the bend, moved out in upper stretch and lacked the needed response. VEGAN stalked the leader inside a pair of rivals, saved ground to the stretch and flattened. PER THE HORSE RACING INTEGRITY AND WELFARE UNIT, KEEP YOUR COIL HAS BEEN DQ'D FOR A POSITIVE TEST.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: JAMMING EDDY chased outside a rival then between foes into the turn, got boxed in at the five-sixteenths pole, altered to the inside approaching the three-sixteenths pole, took over midstretch and drew clear in the end. MONGOLIAN WIND bumped twice leaving the gate, trailed two wide into and around the bend, angled out into the lane and further out in upper stretch, summoned a mild rally and gained the show honors. COMMANDER KHAI raced up close three deep early, chased three deep on the turn then launched a bid outside the top pair and got forced out into the lane, challenged to midstretch and flattened in the final furlong. NEWPARK (IRE) dueled for command from outside, fought three wide around the turn, got floated out by MENDEZ MILE into the lane, fought to midstretch and weakened. MENDEZ MILE dueled inside NEWPARK (IRE) into and around the bend while in the two path, drifted out leaving the turn, lost command at the quarter pole and weakened.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SWIRLING broke in and bumped rival, chased two wide through the turn, closed in approaching the eighth pole, inherited the lead when the leaders fell at the sixteenths pole and was ridden out to the wire. DANCING CRANE got bumped in the beginning, chased on the inside then trailed into the lane and came up empty. TWENTYSEVENTROUTS dueled for command outside FLASHY PASS, put away that rival at the top of the stretch, led clear to the eighth pole, sustained an injury and fell at the sixteenth pole and was vanned off following the race.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SWEET VENGEANCE stalked from inside early, coaxed two wide into the lane, took over past the three-sixteenths and cleared while drifting out, continued to drift in the late stages and was able to hold off the runner-up. RYDER'S CANDY trailed into the turn, went two then three wide around the bend, angled five to six wide into the stretch and further out in the lane, rallied but was too late. ICY BREEZE was off a step slow, tracked two wide into the turn, three wide leaving the bend, angled out into the stretch, closed well then was stymied behind the winner approaching the wire. CHEVY GIRL chased four wide into the turn, had to tip six wide into the lane, challenged in upper stretch but flattened in the late stages. COPPER BO TEN stalked from outside early, went three wide into the turn, took aim at the leader leaving the end and got floated five wide into the drive, challenged in the lane but weakened in the final furlong. FURSACE set the pace up the backstretch, showed the way two wide around the bend before drifting four wide into the lane, lost command past the three-sixteenths pole and weakened.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SONG OF SHADOWS stepped to the front and set the pace two wide into the turn, came out a bit to lead three wide into the drive, responded well when roused and asked left handed and widened in the final furlong. MS MOAB chased two wide into the turn, three wide into the lane and bested the rest. ROSIE ANN RULES raced up close early, took the turn three wide, came four wide into the drive, flattened in the furlong grounds but managed to hold the show. DORINE'S WILD CAT broke a step slow on the outside, chased outside a rival three wide into the turn, came five wide into the drive and lacked a rally. SHAMBALA GIRL broke a step slow, trailed early, rounded the bend four to five wide and failed to menace. DIALING SCOTTY forwardly placed on the inside, saved ground through the turn and weakened down the lane. PERFECT THREAT broke a step slow, raced along the inside and failed to make an impact. DUE TO A TIMER MALFUNCTION, THE HALF-MILE FRACTION WAS HAND-TIMED.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 76. Maiden Claiming Purse 23000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $30,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HALF NELSON set the pace under pressure early, dueled around the turn, battled into the final furlong holding a slim advantage and held gamely to the line. TURQUOISE BIKINI pressed the pace from outside, dueled around the turn and into the lane, hounded the winner through the final furlong and could not get by. LA PALOMA BLANCA stalked widest to the turn, came six wide into the lane, took aim in the lane but lacked the needed late punch. MISS JOANNIE got bumped leaving the gate, stalked two wide into the turn, exited the bend four wide, was in the mix entering the furlong grounds but lacked the needed late punch in deep stretch. VIOLET CROWN broke in and bumped rival, tracked on the inside through the turn and lacked a late bid. ELECTRIC GLIDE bumped leaving he gate, chased three wide into the turn, moved out and entered the stretch five wide and leveled off in the furlong grounds. MISS POLO BAR was off slow and bumped in the beginning, trailed early then three wide near the back into the turn, angled six wide into the lane and failed to menace. BIG UPDATE broke in and bumped rival, chased five then four wide around the bend, drifted inward in the lane and tired. THROW A KANIPCHEN raced off the pace and angled in on the backstretch, trailed into the turn on the inside, drifted into the lane, had little left for the drive, was eased and walked off. DUE TO A TIMER MALFUNCTION, THE SIXTH RACE WAS HAND-TIMED.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: FRENCH ONION vied between foes then inside a pair around the turn, lost touch in upper stretch, came back on in the final sixteenth and bested the runner-up. BURAQ'S REFLECTION vied four deep to the turn, three wide around the bend, took over at the quarter pole, led into the final sixteenth and got outkicked by the winner late. RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 8 1M Dirt CR: 88. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 47000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING OR STARTER OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $40,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Other Than Maiden, Claiming Or Starter At A Mile Or Over Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $40,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GLORIOUS SPRING chased three wide around the first turn, trailed into the second bend, came four wide into the lane, moved out in upper stretch and began to rally, drew alongside the leader at the eighth pole and drove clear. LIBERAL LADY dueled for command in the two path inside a rival, fought along the rail around the far turn, cleared leaving the bend, met the challenge from inner foe with three-sixteenths remaining, clung to a short lead over rivals on both sides at the eighth pole, relinquished the lead to GLORIOUS SPRING shortly after and stayed on to secure second. TROUVILLE antsy in the gate, pulled three then two wide on the first turn, chased two wide around the second bend, moved inside to launch a bid at the three-sixteenths pole but faltered in the final sixteenth. HALOSNHEAVEN was forwardly placed four then three wide on the first turn, dropped back a bit to stalk the top pair outside rivals, spun four wide into the lane and flattened. YOUTEYOURHONOR dueled for the lead outside a rival three wide on the clubhouse turn, fought with LIBERAL LADY to the five-sixteenths pole, chased that rival into the lane, was not persevered with past the three-sixteenths pole, eased in the final furlong and walked off. CHARLOTTE HARBOR was unhurried in the early going from inside, moved closer up the backstretch, lost ground through the far turn, eased in the lane and walked off.
